Employee Management System with JDBC

Description:
This version of the Employee Management System uses JDBC to interact with a MySQL database. It demonstrates the basic operations of inserting, updating, deleting, and displaying employee details. The system also supports sorting based on different employee attributes such as ID, name, age, email, and salary. This project highlights how to handle database connections, prepare statements, and execute SQL queries directly in Java.

Features:
Insert, Update, Delete, and View Employees
Sorting by ID, Name, Age, Email, and Salary
Simple interface with HTML forms
Direct SQL queries using JDBC



Technologies Used:
Java (JDBC)
MySQL
HTML Forms
